The paper deals with the problem of finding optimal paths for a robot in an aisle-graph, which is a type of structure commonly found in warehouses and other industrial settings. This problem is closely related to robotics and automation, which suggests that cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new heuristic algorithm for solving the problem, which involves combining optimal solutions for two special cases of the problem. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves optimization and decision-making, which suggests that it may be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
